<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Apparently, the Burynai Cenobites do NOT drop this belt.  It is dropped by the Burynai GRAND Cenobite.  Don't ask me where he is, though -- I'm not 100% sure.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Bocote FDG</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-05-25 09:24:52</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>The belt is dropped from the named Burnyai "Grand Cenobite".  He is not much harder than a normal Cenobite, and is a rare spawn in Frontier Mountains.  He spawns near the West side of the zone (north of middle).  The tricky part about killing him is avoiding the many giants while engaged.  Let him use his mana on Smites and debuf him for an easier kill.  I was unable to solo him twice being a level 42 druid.  The belt is not druid wearable :(</font></td></tr></table>
